    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="676"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00111 Armament Control/65: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>U.S.S. “<hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >Houston</hi>”</placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1935-10-05">October 5, 1935</date>.<lb/>[Received October 5—4:45
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The facts reported appear to establish the commencement of hostilities and the
                    fact of actual war.</p>
                <p>I agree with Ambassador Long that our neutrality declaration should be issued
                    before action by the League.</p>
                <pb facs="0900" n="798" xml:id="pg_798"/>
                <p>If you have not already taken action you are hereby authorized to do so.</p>
                <closer>[File copy not signed.]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
